==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Centre
<hw>Cen"tre</hw> }</mhw> <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Centered</conjf> or
<conjf>Centred</conjf> <pr>(s⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Centering</conjf> or <conjf>Centring</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To be placed in a center; to be central.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be collected to a point; to be concentrated; to
rest on, or gather about, as a center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where there is no visible truth wherein to <qex>center</qex>,
error is as wide as men's fancies.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H.
More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our hopes must <qex>center</qex> in ourselves alone.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centre</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Center</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>{

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Centre
<hw>Cen"tre</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To place or fix in the center or on a central
point.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To collect to a point; to concentrate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy joys are <qex>centered</qex> all in me alone.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>To form a recess or indentation
for the reception of a center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centrebit</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Centerbit</ent>⟦br⟧
